               <msContents>
                  <summary>A copy, in the hand of Menches, Komogrammateus (village secretary) of Kerkeosiris, of the indictment of certain officials (most likely village secretaries) from three divisions of the nome concerned with the crops, who have apparently made false reports. Appended is a much mutilated note concerning the decision of the superior official upon the case.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Recto and verso published</note>
                     <note type="general">53rd year of Ptolemy VIII Euergetes II, 26th of the Egyptian month Phamenoth.</note>
                     <note type="general">Menches archive</note>
                     <note type="lines">4 cols. (100 lines) on verso across the fibers.</note>
                     <note type="paleography">In regular cursive hand.</note>
                     <note type="recto_verso">On recto: P.Tebt.60 (Summary report on the lands and crops of Kerkeosiris).</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
